---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

const groups = [
  {
    title: 'Environment',
    items: ['Setup YApi', 'Login YApi', 'Who Am I'],
  },
  {
    title: 'Query',
    items: ['Search Interface', 'Get Interface By ID', 'List Category Interfaces'],
  },
  {
    title: 'Docs Sync',
    items: ['Bind Docs Sync', 'Run Docs Sync'],
  },
];
---

<SiteLayout title="Commands | YApi Plugin" description="Command surface for the YApi Cursor plugin.">
  <article class="doc-article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Commands</p>
    <h1>First release command set</h1>
    <p>
      The plugin keeps the command surface small on purpose. Each command maps to one high-value YApi workflow and is
      backed by a local Node wrapper instead of raw shell prompts.
    </p>

    {groups.map((group) => (
      <section class="command-group">
        <h2>{group.title}</h2>
        <ul class="command-list">
          {group.items.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>
    ))}

    <h2>Wrapper behavior</h2>
    <p>
      Commands rely on <code>node scripts/ensure-yapi.mjs</code>, <code>node scripts/setup-yapi.mjs</code>, and
      <code>node scripts/run-yapi.mjs</code> so errors are normalized and Cursor receives stable JSON responses.
    </p>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
